    "attributes": {
        "action": "Review regulations on Battery Energy Storage Systems",
        "additional_details": "These systems have a fire risk due to thermal runaway.\r\nThe fires can be self-sustaining and may last days.\r\nBurning Battery's release hydrogen fluoride which can cause lung damage, severe burns and death.\r\nThere is an explosion risk from this type of battery\r\nWe think we need a minimum distance from the population, strict fire laws should be mandatory and all communities should be consulted.",
        "background": "Review the regulations on Battery Energy Storage System systems, including how close they can be built to homes, schools and hospitals, and rules around safety.",
